title.narrative: Mobile Solutions Technical Assistance and Research (mSTAR) project
Projet d'assistance technique et de recherches de solutions mobiles (mSTAR)
Projeto da assistência técnica e da pesquisa das soluções móveis (mSTAR)

description.narrative: Objectives for Liberia: Planned Outcomes: An approximately 75% reduction in costs related to salary collection for MOE and MOH staff who elect to receive their salaries via mobile money in comparison to the former method; An approximately 75% reduction in time spent collecting salaries for MOE and MOH staff who elect to receive their salaries via mobile money in comparison to the former method; Sustainable and efficient enrollment process for mobile money payment election through GOL payroll established; and ; Increase in understanding for teachers and health workers on mobile money use and benefits.

Le projet d'assistance technique et de recherches de solutions de mobile de FHI 360 (mSTAR) est une larges, flexibles et sensibles assistance technique et programme de recherche qui stimule l'adoption et l'échelle- rapides des finances numériques, de l'inclusion numérique et des données mobiles dans les pays en développement. Finalement, le mSTAR cherche à augmenter l'accès à et l'utilisation du mobile et les technologies numériques par les personnes à faibles revenus, la société civile, les établissements d'administration locale et les dépositaires de secteur privé.

O projeto da assistência técnica e da pesquisa das soluções do móbil de FHI 360 (mSTAR) é uma assistência técnica e um programa de investigação largos, flexíveis e responsivos que esteja promovendo a adoção e a escala-acima rápidas da finança digital, da inclusão digital e de dados móveis em países em vias de desenvolvimento. Finalmente, o mSTAR procura aumentar o acesso a e o uso de tecnologias móveis e digitais por indivíduos a renda baixa, pela sociedade civil, pelas instituições do governo local e pelas partes interessadas do setor privado.

The FHI 360 Mobile Solutions Technical Assistance and Research (mSTAR) project is a broad, flexible and responsive technical assistance and research program that is fostering the rapid adoption and scale-up of digital finance, digital inclusion and mobile data in developing countries. Ultimately, mSTAR seeks to increase access to and use of mobile and digital technologies by low-income individuals, civil society, local government institutions and private-sector stakeholders.
